<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880105-0046 </DOCNO><HL> Raytheon Is Awarded Contracts by Army Totaling $92.8 Million </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RTN MD GQ GE LIT HPC LTV BA </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Raytheon Co. won Army contracts totaling $92.8 million for Hawk missile improvements and Patriot missile parts.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was issued Navy contracts totaling $53.9 million for FA-18aircraft support equipment.    Grumman Corp. got contracts totaling $31.2 million for E-2C aircraft equipment for Egypt through the Navy and space-based particle-beam studies for the Army.    SLI Avionic Systems Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $28 million for C-130navigation system equipment.    Units of General Electric Co. were given contracts totaling $24.8 million for training services for the Army and F-404aircraft engine improvements for the Navy.    Litton Industries Inc. received a $23.4 million Air Force contract for communications equipment.    Hercules Inc. was awarded an $18.7 million Army contract to produce munitions.    LTV Corp. got a $13.6 million Army contract for engineering services.    Boeing Co. was issued Army contracts totaling $11.9 million for simulation services and space-based particle-beam studies. </TEXT></DOC>